HEADWORD: Tremolite
<hw>Trem"o*lite</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From <ets>Tremola</ets>, a
valley in the Alps, where it was discovered.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld>
<def>A white variety of amphibole, or hornblende, occurring in long,
bladelike crystals, and coarsely fibrous masses.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

